                                        1237,
                                        2346,
                                        1976
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Further advancements will require an evolution in the agent's design congruent with specific problems that afflict CC. The literature has shown that ML models can accurately distinguish between packet loss attributable to congestion or channel errors. We plan to integrate a similar classifier within MARLIN and investigate the feasibility of an analogous approach to identify variations in end- to- end latency that are caused by changes in the path to destination. The fundamental building block of CC algorithms is how and when to change the CwND size. MARLIN currently actively controls the \"how\", leaving the \"when\" to a heuristic. We will investigate learning- based approaches to include such decision factor into MARLIN, with the goal of turning it into a more comprehensive and reactive system, able to make rational decisions at its own tempo."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 13
                },
                {
